  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 22-26.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The case of a ruler or nobleman. The clause, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Or if his sin...  come to his knowledge",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", should be rather translated, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "If perhaps his sin come to his knowledge.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " He is to offer ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "a kid of the goats",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or rather a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "he-goat.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The blood is not to be carried into the tabernacle, as in the two previous cases, but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "put upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which stood outside in the court, and, as a consequence of the blood not having been taken into the tabernacle, the flesh is not to be burnt outside the camp, but to be eaten by the priests in the court of the tabernacle (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 6:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Leviticus 4:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
